Overview
This project is a web-based weather application that allows users to get current weather information for any city. The application is built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and it uses a weather API to fetch the data.

Features
Search Functionality: Users can search for current weather information by city name.
Weather Details: Displays temperature, weather conditions, humidity, and wind speed.
Responsive Design: Adapts to various screen sizes and devices.
Dynamic Background: Changes background based on weather conditions (optional).
Technologies Used
HTML5: For the structure of the web page.
CSS3: For styling and layout.
JavaScript: For fetching data from the weather API and updating the DOM.
Weather API: To fetch current weather data.
HTML
The index.html file contains the structure of the web page, including the search form and weather display area.
CSS
The styles.css file includes the following:

Base Styles: Basic styling for body, headings, buttons, etc.
Layout: Flexbox for centering the content and elements.
Responsive Design: Media queries to adjust the layout for different screen sizes.
JavaScript
The script.js file includes:

Fetch Weather Data: JavaScript to fetch weather data from the API.
Update DOM: JavaScript to update the DOM elements with the fetched weather data.
Event Listener: JavaScript to handle the form submission and fetch data based on the input city.
